getInitialEventSelect

public java.util.List<InitialEventSelect> getInitialEventSelect()
Gets the value of the initialEventSelect property.

This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the initialEventSelect property.

For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

    getInitialEventSelect().add(newItem);

Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list InitialEventSelect
